HEADWORD: Microseism
<hw>Mi"cro*seism</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Micro-</ets> + Gr. <?/ an earthquake, fr. <?/ to
shake.]</ety> <def>A feeble earth tremor not directly perceptible, but
detected only by means of specially constructed apparatus.</def> --
<wordforms><wf>Mi`cro*seis"mic</wf> <pr>(#)</pr>,
<wf>Mi`cro*seis"mic*al</wf> <pr>(#)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
